        <div class="item-info">
                <div class="slug-wrap">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/thesalt/">The Salt</a></h3>
                </div>

            <h2 class="title"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/thesalt/2012/06/07/154510881/our-obama-family-dinner-survey-shows-brown-rice-is-still-a-tough-sell"  data-metrics='{"action":"Click Story Title","category":"Story List"}' >Our Obama Family Dinner Survey Shows Brown Rice Is Still A Tough Sell</a></h2>
            
            
            <p class="teaser"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/thesalt/2012/06/07/154510881/our-obama-family-dinner-survey-shows-brown-rice-is-still-a-tough-sell"><time datetime="2012-06-08"><span class="date">June 8, 2012 &#149; </span></time>Say the words "brown rice," and people of a certain age might conjure images of hippie communes. But the whole-grain product has been slowly gaining in popularity over the last decade. Here are some tips to bring it into the everyday dinner repertoire.</a></p>

            

        </div>
        
